HEADWORD: Tournois
<hw>Tour`nois"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., belonging
to <ets>Tours</ets> in France.]</ety> <def>A former French money of
account worth 20 sous, or a franc. It was thus called in distinction
from the Paris <xex>livre</xex>, which contained 25 sous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tournure</ent>⟦br⟧
